                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Griscom</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-04-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 6, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Griscom says, regarding the proposals of Italian minister for foreign
                    affairs (Signor Tittoni) concerning The Hague Conference, he may add that Signor
                    Tittoni told him informally that the Italian delegates to the conference would
                    neither take part in the discussion nor vote on the question of limitation of
                    armaments.)</p>
            </div>
